<div class="a-section">
  What's in a filter? I can tell a difference between tap water (Maryland/Virginia suburbs) and filtered water. However, I'm not so much a water snob that I care between filtered water and bottled water (Fiji etc.). So long as my filtered water doesn't taste like tap, I'm happy. The Best MWF filter looks like my GE MWF filters. It comes wrapped and has a cover on the filter threaded end. It's supposed to be NSF certified like my GE filter and costs 1/3 of the price. It fits just as well as my GE filter and doesn't leak. The taste is the same in my opinion, which is basically water with no taste. After running a few gallons through, everything seems the same from taste to water flow. I say this is a winner and a real bargain price. I'll update if it doesn't seem to last as long as my GE filters, but even those I reset the filter light once or twice before replacing. I received this item for free in exchange for an honest review.
</div>

