<div class="a-section">
  This aftermarket or non-OEM water filter replaces the GE MWF filters. I did not notice a difference between my original GE MWF filter and this Best GE MWF filter in terms of taste. They are very similar might not be equivalent. The GE filters are NSF certified and claims to filters a few more things that the Best Filter does not claim to filter. Those things include ibuprofen, progesterone, atenolol, trimethoprim and fluoxetine, cysts, asbestos.<br><br>Both of the filters are supposed to last 6 months. It is recommended to follow the 6 months rule unless if you use a ton of water and know that you are using more than 300 gallons during the 6 months. Filters tend to absorb a limited amount of chemicals for a period of time then slowly releases them after it&#8217;s full or expired. Overusing filters do not help and they may make the water worse than directly from the tap.<br><br>I originally switched to Brita water filters and pitchers because of price and my GE refrigerator&#8217;s water line froze. I figured it wasn&#8217;t work the hassle of fixing the water line and using filters for pitchers were cheaper than a replacement GE MWF filter. The filters made by GE will cost about $50, which is a huge difference when comparing it to other non-OEM filters. Using these cheaper filters makes it unnecessary to have a slow pitcher for water.<br><br>I received this product for free or at a discounted price in exchange for an unbiased and honest review.
</div>

